latestIgtvVideos.title: The Bush beckons: South Africa Tourism
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Surrender to the charm of South African Safaris and Sunsets

Take a walk on the wild side with luxurious and opulent game lodges and the abundant African game– a perfect bridge between limitless comfort and the wild. Luxury properties offer the perfect socially distanced getaway, complete with Big 5 sightings, indigenous performances, lavish spa treatments and photography lessons.
After dusk, guests are offered one of the most authentic South African food experiences – Boma dining (a boma is an open-air reed fenced area). It is a traditional dining experience complete with traditional song and dance, drumming sessions, sundowners and delicious braais (barbeques) under the South African starry sky – which is said to be one of the best in the world!

Extreme E Sports has a new address... @experiencealula
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Extreme E Sports has a new address... 
AlUla, is a city of the Medina Region in north-western Saudi Arabia which historically located on the incense route. 
AlUla is hosting Extreme E sporting race which is happening from April 3 to 5. With ten teams ready to compete, fielding a legendary line-up of champion drivers, the series is gearing up for an epic opening weekend of action when it all kicks off in AlUla, Saudi Arabia. Jensen Button, Lewis Hamilton are some of the names involved in this iconic race. 
Not only will Extreme E bring short, sharp wheel-to-wheel racing to a global audience through its more than 40 international broadcasters, it has a wider purpose – to highlight the climate emergency affecting everybody worldwide. Through motorsport, the series will showcase electric SUVs racing in some of the most remote corners of the planet that have all been damaged by climate change.

As the holiday season twinkles to life, there’s nothing quite like the aroma of freshly brewed coffee to warm your heart and lift your spirits. Whether you’re wrapped in a blanket by the fireplace or hosting a cheerful Christmas get-together, these festive coffee recipes are the perfect way to brew joy and cheer!

Curated by Shreya Sanghvi and Simran Vohra, Recipe Curators at NUUK, these creations are packed with flavors of the season, making every sip a celebration. ☕✨

Let’s brew, blend, and sip our way through these delicious Christmas delights! 
@theunoplate @diet_by_simran_vohra

1. Coffee Chia Pudding
A wholesome treat that brings together coffee, texture, and a touch of sweetness.
Ingredients: Espresso, chia seeds, milk, sweetener, vanilla, almonds.
Let it sit overnight and wake up to pure festive bliss!

2. Rich and Creamy Hot Chocolate Cappuccino
A luxurious blend of espresso, rich chocolate, and warm spices.
 Ingredients: Espresso, milk, chocolate, cinnamon, cocoa, cornstarch.
Top with whipped cream, marshmallows, and strawberries for a magical treat!

3. Salted Caramel Cinnamon Latte
A frosty delight that combines sweet, salty, and spiced flavors.
Ingredients: Milk, espresso, salted caramel, cinnamon, nutmeg, sea salt, ice.
Blend it up, top with whipped cream and caramel drizzle, and enjoy!

Raise your mugs to the season of joy, warmth, and delicious coffee! 

#BrewTheCheer #FestiveCoffee #ChristmasCoffees #NUUKRecipes #HolidaySips #IndiaTodaySpice

As 2024 wraps up, it’s time to swap the daily hustle for twinkling lights, cozy evenings, and merry celebrations. Whether you’re hosting a glamorous soirée or enjoying a snug night in, these festive cocktails by Pallav Soin, Chief Revenue Officer, Modi Illva, are sure to set the mood.

Let’s shake, stir, and sip our way through these delightful recipes! 

1. Santa’s Secret Sazerac
A sophisticated cocktail to add warmth to your holidays.
Ice cubes | 1 tsp sugar syrup | 3 dashes Angostura bitters | 20 ml Rockford Whisky | 1 tsp anise | Lemon peel strip

Mixing Magic:
1️⃣ Chill a tumbler with ice. In a separate glass, combine sugar syrup, bitters, and whisky; stir.
2️⃣ Coat the chilled glass with anise, then strain the whisky mix in.
3️⃣ Rub lemon peel along the rim and drop it in. Cheers! 🥃🎄

2. Winter Wonderland Whisky
A timeless classic with a refreshing, festive twist!
1 part Rockford Whisky | 4 parts Quality Ginger Ale | 1 Lime Wedge

Mixing Magic:
1️⃣ Fill a glass with ice, pour whisky, and top with ginger ale.
2️⃣ Squeeze lime over the drink and drop it in. Sip and enjoy! ❄️✨

 3. Winter Orchard Delight
A beautiful infusion bursting with festive flavors.
1/2 Green Apple, sliced | 🍎 1/2 Red Apple, sliced | 🍋 1/2 Lemon, sliced | 2 Cinnamon Sticks | 60 ml Artic Vodka

Mixing Magic:
1️⃣ Combine fruits and cinnamon in a jar.
2️⃣ Pour vodka, shake gently, and refrigerate for 24 hours. Serve chilled! 🍂🍸

4. Twisted Whisky Sour
A zesty spin on a timeless favorite.
45 ml Rockford Whisky | 🍊 30 ml Orange Juice | 🍋 20 ml Lime Juice | 15 ml Sugar Syrup | 2-3 Drops Aromatic Bitters | Ice Cubes

Mixing Magic:
1️⃣ Fill a tin with ice, add whisky, juices, sugar syrup, and bitters.
2️⃣ Shake well, strain over ice, and garnish with orange or cherry. Cheers! 🍹🎉

Raise your glass to good times, great company, and delicious drinks! 🥂✨

#IndiaTodaySpice #FestiveCocktails #CheersToTheSeason #HolidayDrinks #RaiseAToast

Apple’s MacBook Pro 14-inch 2024 might look familiar, but under the hood, it’s a whole new world. Think of it as a classic novel rewritten with a plot twist — familiar cover, mind-blowing content.

By Sulabh Puri @sulabh.puri 

Sleeker and Smarter
Apple sticks to its sleek design playbook, offering the MacBook Pro in Space Black and Silver. While the aesthetics are familiar, the real magic is under the hood. The Liquid Retina XDR display is now brighter than ever, hitting 1,000 nits for both HDR and SDR content. The new nano-texture option reduces glare so effectively that you’ll wonder if it also deflects unwanted attention.

More Power, Less Drama
Powered by the new M4 family of chips built on enhanced 3-nanometer technology, this MacBook Pro delivers performance that could make desktop PCs nervous. With up to a 10-core CPU and 10-core GPU in the M4, multitasking feels like a leisurely stroll. Enhanced machine learning accelerators and a faster Neural Engine mean it’s not just smart — it’s genius.

Answering Our Need for Speed
Models with M4 Pro or M4 Max chips now support Thunderbolt 5, offering transfer speeds of up to 120Gb/s. Wi-Fi 6E and Bluetooth 5.3 ensure that you’re connected faster than a teenager to free Wi-Fi. And let’s not forget the upgraded 12MP Center Stage camera, which keeps you in focus even when life doesn’t.

Our Verdict
With up to 24 hours of battery life, it might just outlast your favourite series binge. It’s a powerhouse wrapped in elegance, making it indispensable for pros and creators alike. In a nutshell, it’s the same MacBook Pro you love, but turbocharged for the future.

Price: ₹2,84,900

To read more, grab our latest issue now. Out on stands! 📖📰

Pick Of The Day: Zenith Unveils the Limited-Edition Defy Extreme Jungle @zenithwatches 

Limited to just 50 pieces, the DEFY Extreme Jungle is the final chapter in ZENITH’s trilogy of 1/100th of a second chronographs inspired by extreme environments. Following the Desert and Glacier editions, this bold timepiece channels the untamed energy of the jungle.

Crafted from brushed titanium, the 45mm case features Tiger’s Eye accents, showcasing natural golden-brown hues that evoke the strength and mystique of a tiger. A true blend of creativity and performance, the watch is engineered to withstand both wilderness adventures and urban challenges, with water resistance up to 20 ATM.

latestPosts.caption:
THE AUDI Q8 IS ONE STEALTHY PIECE OF WORK
@audi 

By Meraj Shah @mayradge 

Think James Bond at a black-tie affair: sophisticated, dandy, charming but with just enough subtle menace to remind everyone that he could throw a punch if he had to. And when he leaves, Bond drives off in a car that looks like it could slip through the valet’s grip as nonchalantly as it would conquer a mountain pass. That car, if you’ve conjured one in your mind’s eye, would be the Audi Q8.

It’s a flattering personification, no question. But the Q8 makes a strong case with its contrarian virtues: a nimble grand tourer masquerading as an SUV, it sits tall, but feels taut and balanced like a sports car once you get going. It proceeds in very civilized fashion: quiet, non-intrusive; the engine humming along discreetly. But when you call upon it—say, for a quick overtake on a winding country road—it drops this sophisticated facade and shows its true strength.

To read more, grab our latest issue now — out on stands! 📰
